Kowloon's Wardens of Iron share provisioning doctrine and emergency charter frameworks with Midgaard's Guard Command under a formal bilateral agreement that includes mutual recognition of Knight credentials. Knights operating in Kowloon under Warden of Iron auspices encounter a different institutional culture: the Wardens' governance is more explicitly labor-relations oriented, and tactical command chains are complicated by Kowloon's district-color governance structure, which gives the five civic institutions overlapping jurisdictions that don't always map cleanly onto tactical command hierarchies. The Compact's principle — doctrine over employer — manifests differently in Kowloon, where "employer" is ambiguous when five institutions each have partial jurisdiction over the same operational space. Warden of Iron officers who are Knight-trained have developed informal protocols for resolving these overlapping authority questions that exist parallel to the formal governance structure.

