Mafdet's Harbor Wardens maintain a maritime escort function that draws on Knight training through a separate institutional framework from the inland equivalent. Maritime convoy escort has formation discipline requirements analogous to road escort but adapted to shipboard and dock conditions: smaller formation sizes, different terrain constraints, and the specific tactical demands of boarding-and-repelling scenarios that road escort does not encounter. Mafdet recognizes Knight academy credentials but requires supplementary maritime escort certification for practitioners in Harbor Warden service. The Strandline Compact's trade network generates consistent demand for Knight-trained escort personnel at scales that make Mafdet one of the larger employers of the tradition in the five-city network despite its smaller civic size.

