Ashborn forge-culture approaches Knight formation doctrine with a specific practical orientation: formations are structures that succeed through correct construction and fail through structural weakness. The Compact's three-principle motto — break, hold, recover — maps onto forge-work structure: the breaking force is the striking blow, the holding discipline is the temper that keeps the blade from shattering, and the recovery commitment is the reforging when the work is damaged. Ashborn Knights in Midgaard's Guard Command tend toward the defensive discipline end of the formation spectrum — the holding principle resonates with Ashborn patience in the forge-work process more than the aggressive forward-movement principle. Guard Command officers note that Ashborn Knights are exceptionally reliable in sustained siege defense contexts and require more encouragement than average in rapid aggressive advance scenarios.

